The paper focuses on multi-hop textual question answering, which is a subfield of natural language processing and falls under the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The model also involves retrieving and using additional knowledge, which can be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
